    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1131: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-01T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. No report has been received from you since your 67 September 8, 11 a.m.,<note
                        n="27" xml:id="d163fn27">Not printed.</note> regarding daily deposits.
                    Department informed by railway company that it fears deposits on hand may be
                    withdrawn if remittances to London not promptly made. Report by cable on daily
                    deposits and what, if any, remittances to London on account of railway bonds
                    have been made. Report also your recommendations with reference to what
                    representations, if any, should be made to Ecuadorean Government in the
                    premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
